  "prompt": "How do you pronounce PostgreSQL?",
  "response": "\"PostgreSQL\" is pronounced as \"post-gres-Q-L.\" Here's a breakdown of the pronunciation:\n\n- **Post**: This part is pronounced like the word \"post\" (as in \"mail post\").\n- **gres**: This part is pronounced like \"gres\" (rhymes with \"dress\").\n- **Q**: This is simply pronounced as the letter \"Q.\"\n- **L**: This is simply pronounced as the letter \"L.\"\n\nSo, when you put it all together, it sounds like \"post-gres-Q-L.\" Some people also refer to it as simply \"Postgres\" for short, which is pronounced \"post-gres.\" \n\nBoth pronunciations are widely accepted in the community.",
